<hl>
<seg id=1> Huang Sihua: Create A Better Environment Next Year; Malaysia Wants to Retain 10 Billion Foreign Capitals in Stock Market. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (Kuala Lumpur) - Huang Sihua, Vice Financial Minister of Malaysia, said that it is anticipated that over 10 billion ringgit of foreign capital could be withdrawn from the stock market when foreign currency control measurement enters its one full year by September 1 next year. Therefore, the government will take all possible measures to create a better investment environment to encourage foreign capital's retaining in Malaysia. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> He said, from the economic growth rate of the third quarter, we can see that Malaysia's economy has showed its sign of revival, it is believed that by September next year the economy will tend to stable, and the market will have come alive and foreign businessmen will invest to Malaysia again. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Huang Sihua made a speech on an economic report and communion meeting held by Malaysia Chinese Industrial and Commercial Union the day before yesterday. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> He stressed that Malaysian government will fix the exchange rate for Malaysian currency at 1 USD = 3.8 ringgit. This will encourage the investors to map out a long-term investment plan, make more correct investment decision without worrying about the fluctuation of currency exchange rate. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> He said, the foreign currency control measures would be taken for some time until international currency market is stable. A speculation control system and transparency of currency trade would be established internationally and to be perfectly executed to prevent Southeast Asia from attack of financial storm again. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> On the other hand, Huang Sihua said, through the coordination of Ministry of Finance, our country has approved the loan to 20% companies whose loan application was not approved before and complained to Ministry of Finance. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> He said, Ministry of Finance will continue to offer consulting or relevant assistance to those companies with their loan application not approved, to enable those companies to carry out their developing plans smoothly and as a result, to drive the domestic economic market activities. </seg>
</p>
